When serving files using the `Directory` resource in Restlet 2.3.7 I get an NPE if the URL contains a query. Before the `DirectoryServerResource` refactoring this worked fine and `DirectoryServerResource` would just ignore the query.

The NPE is caused by https://github.com/restlet/restlet-framework-java/blob/2.3.7/modules/org.restlet/src/org/restlet/engine/local/DirectoryServerResource.java#L199 assigning `null` to `this.relativePart` which is then accessed on line 203.

I think it is caused by `Reference#getRemainingRef()` which seems to return `null` when there is a query argument: 
The url `http://myapplication/fichier.txt` gives `fichier.txt` as remaining ref 
The url `http://myapplication/fichier.txt?x=y` gives `null` as remaining ref while I would expect this to also be `fichier.txt` or `fichier.txt?x=y`. (this was observed using the test case described below)

